{"atom_id": "ig34_p0302_a012", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 302, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.3.7.5 Ophthalmic Examinations (OE)", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "This example shows:", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.3", "ts": "2026-04-27T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0302_a013", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 302, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.3.7.5 Ophthalmic Examinations (OE)", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Different assessments, from the front to the back of the eye, for 1 subject at 1 visit", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.3", "ts": "2026-04-27T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0302_a014", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 302, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.3.7.5 Ophthalmic Examinations (OE)", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "The use of the supplemental qualifier non-standard variable (NSV) OEEDILST (Eye Dilation Status)", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.3", "ts": "2026-04-27T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0302_a015", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 302, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.3.7.5 Ophthalmic Examinations (OE)", "atom_type": "SENTENCE", "verbatim": "The test for iris color is in the OE domain because in this use case, the medication is likely to change the result over the course of the study. Otherwise, iris color should be represented in the Subject Characteristics (SC) domain (see Section 6.3.10, Subject Characteristics).", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": ["§6.3.10"], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.3", "ts": "2026-04-27T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0302_a016", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 302, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.3.7.5 Ophthalmic Examinations (OE)", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Rows 1-2: Show assessments of the color of the iris (OELOC=\"IRIS\") for the right and left eyes, respectively.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.3", "ts": "2026-04-27T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0302_a017", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 302, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.3.7.5 Ophthalmic Examinations (OE)", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Rows 3-4: Show assessments of the status of the lens (OELOC=\"LENS\") for the right and left eyes, respectively. This status assessment is to determine whether the lens of the eye is the natural lens (OEORRES=\"PHAKIC\") or a replacement (OEORRES=\"PSEUDOPHAKIC\").", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.3", "ts": "2026-04-27T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0302_a018", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 302, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.3.7.5 Ophthalmic Examinations (OE)", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Rows 5-6: Show assessments looking for the presence of hyperemia (increased blood flow). The fact that OELOC=\"CONJUNCTIVA\" even for the left eye, where hyperemia was absent, suggests that this examination was specifically an examination of the conjunctiva. Hyperemia was identified in the right eye and was judged to be clinically significant.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.3", "ts": "2026-04-27T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0302_a019", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 302, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.3.7.5 Ophthalmic Examinations (OE)", "atom_type": "LIST_ITEM", "verbatim": "Rows 7-8: Show measurements of the cup-to-disc ratio for the right and left eyes, respectively.", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.3", "ts": "2026-04-27T00:00:00Z"}}
