{"atom_id": "ig34_p0305_a020", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 305, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.3.7.6 Reproductive System Findings (RP)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| USUBJID | Unique Subject Identifier | Char | | Identifier | Identifier used to uniquely identify a subject across all studies for all applications or submissions involving the product. | Req |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.3", "ts": "2026-04-27T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0305_a021", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 305, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.3.7.6 Reproductive System Findings (RP)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| RPSEQ | Sequence Number | Num | | Identifier | Sequence number to ensure uniqueness of records within a dataset for a subject (or within a parameter, in the case of the Trial Summary domain). May be any valid number including decimals and does not have to start at 1. | Req |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.3", "ts": "2026-04-27T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0305_a022", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 305, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.3.7.6 Reproductive System Findings (RP)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| RPGRPID | Group ID | Char | | Identifier | Optional group identifier, used to link together a block of related records within a subject in a domain. Also used to link together a block of related records in the Trial Summary domain. | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.3", "ts": "2026-04-27T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0305_a023", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 305, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.3.7.6 Reproductive System Findings (RP)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| RPREFID | Reference ID | Char | | Identifier | Identifier for the RPREFERENCE ID. Used for an ECG waveform or a medical imaging ID. UBID for reference to multiple studies across domains. This may be a one-to-one or a one-to-many relationship. | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.3", "ts": "2026-04-27T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0305_a024", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 305, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.3.7.6 Reproductive System Findings (RP)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| RPSPID | Sponsor-Defined Identifier | Char | | Identifier | Sponsor-defined identifier. Example: Preprinted line identifier on a CRF. | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.3", "ts": "2026-04-27T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0305_a025", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 305, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.3.7.6 Reproductive System Findings (RP)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| RPLNKID | Link ID | Char | | Identifier | Identifier used to link related records across domains. This may be a one-to-one or a one-to-many relationship. | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.3", "ts": "2026-04-27T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0305_a026", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 305, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.3.7.6 Reproductive System Findings (RP)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| RPLNKGRP | Link Group ID | Char | | Identifier | Identifier used to link related records across domains. This will usually be a many-to-one relationship. | Perm |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.3", "ts": "2026-04-27T00:00:00Z"}}
{"atom_id": "ig34_p0305_a027", "source": "SDTMIG_v3.4", "page": 305, "page_region": "middle", "parent_section": "§6.3.7.6 Reproductive System Findings (RP)", "atom_type": "TABLE_ROW", "verbatim": "| RPTEST (RP) | Short Name of Reproductive Test | Char | (RPESTCD) | Topic | Short character value for a short name of a dataset from a narrow collection into a horizontal format. The short value can be up to 8 characters. Examples: \"CHILDPOT\", \"BCMETHOD\", \"MENARGAE\". | Req |", "heading_level": null, "sibling_index": null, "figure_ref": null, "cross_refs": [], "extracted_by": {"subagent_type": "oh-my-claudecode:writer", "prompt_version": "P0_writer_pdf_v1.3", "ts": "2026-04-27T00:00:00Z"}}
